# Installing a Code Editor

Now that you have Node.js installed, you need a place to write your code.

## Option 1: Cursor (Recommended for Beginners)

Cursor is an AI-powered code editor that helps you write code faster with built-in AI assistance.

1. Go to [cursor.com](https://cursor.com)
2. Download the version for your operating system
3. Install and open it

{% card title="Why Cursor?" variant="feature" %}
Cursor is perfect for beginners because:
- Built-in AI can explain code and help you learn
- It can generate code from natural language descriptions
- Excellent autocomplete suggestions
- Based on VS Code, so it's familiar to many developers
{% /card %}

## Option 2: Visual Studio Code

If you prefer a traditional editor without AI features:

1. Go to [code.visualstudio.com](https://code.visualstudio.com)
2. Download the version for your operating system
3. Install and open it

