# Testing Your Setup

Let's create a simple project to verify everything works!

## Step 1: Create a Project Folder

Open your terminal and run:

```bash
mkdir my-first-project
cd my-first-project
```

## Step 2: Initialize the Project

```bash
npm init -y
```

This creates a `package.json` file that tracks your project's dependencies.

## Step 3: Create Your First File

In your code editor, create a new file called `index.js` in the `my-first-project` folder with this content:

```javascript
console.log("Hello! Your development environment is working!");
```

## Step 4: Run Your Code

In the terminal, make sure you're in the project folder and run:

```bash
node index.js
```

You should see: `Hello! Your development environment is working!`

{% callout type="success" title="Congratulations!" %}
You've successfully set up your development environment and run your first JavaScript code!
{% /callout %}

